text.tspan: The Tarazuku Revue, an all-female theater troupe, is often
cited as an inspiration for Boys Love manga. The group fea
tures women in male roles, playing with gender bending and
androgyny. Osamu Tezuka was inspired by this group, and
went on to write Princess Knight in 1953, which tells the story
of a girl who is raised as a boy.
